name: gnumpy
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "gnumpy" %}
{% set version = "0.2" %}

package:
  name: '{{ name|lower }}'
  version: '{{ version }}'

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 070b78ee648c42e3dcd2f56a4308cc26bcaa1de30a4f7c078eb5828050a4ec4f

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python <3
  run:
    - python <3
    - numpy

test:
  imports:
    - gnumpy

about:
  home: http://www.cs.toronto.edu/~tijmen/gnumpy.html
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Similar to numpy but computes on GPUs by using Cudamat
  description: Similar to numpy but computes on GPUs by using Cudamat

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - nick-youngblut
